Angular 9.0.3

I'm trying to protect user routes. To do so I created an AuthGuardMiddleware and implemented to routes. But I'm able to view only one component. Even if I logged in, all i do just able to view redirected component. If I click the other routes, neither throws error nor renders the component. Nothing happens. 

```js
const routes: Routes = [
  {path: '', canActivate: [AuthGuardMiddleware], component: TasksComponent},
  {path: 'create', canActivate: [AuthGuardMiddleware], component: TaskCreateComponent},
  {path: 'edit/:id', canActivate: [AuthGuardMiddleware], component: TaskEditComponent, resolve: {task: TaskResolver}},
  {path: 'lists', canActivate: [AuthGuardMiddleware], component: TaskListsComponent},
];
```
inside of AuthGuardMiddleware
```js
  canActivate(): Observable<boolean | UrlTree> {
    return this.authService.user.pipe(
      take(1),
      map(user => {
      if (user) {
        return true;
      }
      return this.router.createUrlTree(['/login']);
    }));
  }
```
I realized that when I clean up my app component and remove conditional router outlet, everything start to work fine. I still don't know what exactly causing this error.
app component

```js
export class AppComponent implements OnInit {
  currentUrl: string;
  isAuthRoute = false;

  constructor(private router: Router) {
  }

  ngOnInit() {
    this.router.events.subscribe(event => {
      if (event instanceof NavigationEnd) {
        this.currentUrl = event.url;
        this.isAuthRoute = ['/login', '/register']
          .indexOf(this.currentUrl) !== -1;
      }
    });
  }
}
```
